          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex> be a complex of cosimplicial sheaves on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>, endowed with an increasing filtration <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex>.
    We define the <fr:em>diagonal filtration</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\delta (W,L)]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> to be the increasing filtration of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {s} K]]></fr:tex> given by

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2432</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.1.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>7.1.6.1</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         \begin {aligned}           \delta (W,L)_n(\mathrm {s} K)           &= \bigoplus _{p,q} W_{n+p}(K^{p,q})         \\&= \sum _p \mathrm {s}(W_{n+p}(K)) \cap  L^p(\mathrm {s} K).         \end {aligned}       \tag{7.1.6.1}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:p>
            <fr:p>We have

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2433</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.2</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.2.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>7.1.6.2</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         \operatorname {Gr}_n^{\delta (W,L)}(\mathrm {s} K)         \simeq  \bigoplus _p \operatorname {Gr}_{n+p}^W(K^{\bullet  p})[-p].       \tag{7.1.6.2}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:p>
            <fr:p>The functor <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(K,W)\mapsto (\mathrm {s} K,\delta (W,L))]]></fr:tex> sends filtered quasi-isomorphisms to filtered quasi-isomorphisms, and defines

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2434</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.3</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.3.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>7.1.6.3</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         \begin {aligned}           (s,\delta )           \colon  \mathrm {D}^+\mathrm {F}(S_\bullet )           &\to  \mathrm {D}^+\mathrm {F}(S)         \\(K,W)           &\mapsto  (\mathrm {s} K,\delta (W,L))         \end {aligned}       \tag{7.1.6.3}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

    whence, by composition with <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-7.1.5.1" href="hodge-theory-iii-7.1.5.1.xml" taxon="Equation" number="7.1.5.1" />,

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2435</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.4</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.4.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>7.1.6.4</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         \begin {aligned}           (\mathrm {R}\Gamma ,\delta (-,L))           \colon  \mathrm {D}^+\mathrm {F}(X_\bullet )           &\to  \mathrm {D}^+\mathrm {F}(S)         \\(K,W)           &\mapsto  (\mathrm {R}\Gamma  K,\delta (W,L)).         \end {aligned}       \tag{7.1.6.4}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

    From <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.2" href="hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.2.xml" taxon="Equation" number="7.1.6.2" />, we see that

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2436</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.5</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.5.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>7.1.6.5</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         \operatorname {Gr}_n^{\delta (W,L)}         = \bigoplus _p \mathrm {R}{a_p}_*(\operatorname {Gr}_{n+p}^W K)[-p].       \tag{7.1.6.5}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
